> speech_prog doors? door? doors. door. doors door~
mpechoat $n The bartender looks over to you, he must have overheard you.
whisper $n You know that door over there to the west side of the room?
mpechoat $n _whi Well, that was here even before I got here.  This inn is really owned by the King and all them.  I just think it's weird when I'm unable to take a look at a door in my own inn.  They're blocking it basically.  Wonder what's behind it...
if class($n) == Warrior
mpechoat $n _whi You know, you are a warrior yourself, perhaps you could get more out of them then I can.  I overheard a word once, it was "ztgythkgn".  It means "strength" to humans in orcish language, and that's about all I know.
endif
