E
'garlac' 'book' 'alchemy' 'midas' 'touch'~
"You find a particularly interesting section in the book..."
 
...the midas touch spell as being arguably the greatest trick
an alchemist has.  My own findings on the spell find it to be
an often unreliable spell, as the item must have some sort of
real value to succeed, which can reduce the overall use of this
spell to not much importance at all, but merely a parlor trick
or a way to get rid of found equipment quickly and efficiently.
 
After quite a many of extensive testing with this spell, I
believe I have proven that not only the object is required to
have a real value, but the gold amount that any given item
is turned to is exactly half of that initial value...
 
"hmm....fascinating......"
~
