#11232
academy book~
a book entitled "You're Out of the Academy, Now What?"~
A book to help people fresh from the academy is here.~
~
34 0 1
0 0 0 0
1 0 0 101
E
'academy' 'book'~
So you've made your way out of the academy, and are probably
wondering what to do now.  Well, the first thing to do was head
to the library, which you've obviously done.  While you're there,
you'll want to absorb all the literature you can stand, and put
together some sort of information database in your head, because
the most trivial-seeming thing found in a book may prove handy
some day.
 
Most newbies are eager to just level and nothing more, which is fine.
If this fits you, then put this book back and head to the west side of
town where you'll find the town well.  Go down that and you'll enter
into the sewers where you can further fight to gain in experience.
 
If you can spare a bit more time, you might want to choose a god
to devote yourself to (see help deity), set your title, and
take a look around town to get a good idea where things are located.

You'll probably need some better equipment, so try going east just
once from Town Square Central (TSC) and you'll find a chain of
three stores, armor, weapons, and jewelry.

If you're needy, then try the donation room in the church also
east of here.  Sometimes people may leave things there for people
like you, and hopefully someday you will too.

You can buy water flasks and torches at the general store near the
southwestern corner of town, in the gardens.
corner of town, in the gardens.
Food can be purchased just a few rooms east of this library at
the bakery.
~
#11233
pamphlet stores~
a pamphlet on stores~
A small pamphlet about stores is here.~
~
34 0 1
0 0 0 0
1 0 0 101
E
'pamphlet' 'stores' 'store'~
This is a short pamphlet on information on stores in the world of
Amethyst.
 
Stores naturally are places anywhere in the world where one may
purchase things with value.  This includes the shops you would
find in a city like New Hope, and the trading post in the woods.
 
Some notes on shops:
 *Some items have no value, since not everything you find or have
  has any cost, and therefor is worth nothing except in auction
  or if you find someone to buy it directly from you.
 *Rarely do shops buy things back from people.  The weapondealer,
  Thorne doesn't need nor want your junk, he has his own
  inventory.  Some businesses like the pawn shop however specialize
  in second-hand merchandise, and would be glad to pay you for it.
 *_NEVER_ attack a shopkeeper.  They are too important to the world
  to just die at the hands of some irate robber like yourself, and
  it is almost a gurantee that they have been attempted to be robbed
  before and know how to deal with you in a quick and probably
  painful manner.
 *It's often best to shop around before buying something if you're
  hard on cash.  Stores in different locations can have different
  price rates, some shopkeepers are able to inflate prices because
  of their in-town location, while a store out aways from town
  may sell something similar or exactly the same for a cheaper price.
 *Stores have closing and opening times, because no one wants to
  work 24 hours a day.  In most shops there will be a sign that
  tells these exact times so that you will know when to come back
  if you've happened along at a post-hours time.
 *Please note that prices in all stores are based upon your level,
  higher level means a slight increase in the price.  This is to
  insure that the economy is kept stable.
 *Also know that most shops that buy things from people only have
  as much money as they make, if no one buys from the store
  then that store will have no money to buy things.
~
